{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":627,"text":"I was born in Den Bosch,"},{"time":2263,"text":"where the painter Hieronymus Bosch\nnamed himself after."},{"time":5624,"text":"And I've always been very fond\nof this painter"},{"time":8071,"text":"who lived and worked in the 15th century."},{"time":10580,"text":"And what is interesting about him\nin relation to morality"},{"time":13300,"text":"is that he lived at a time\nwhere religion's influence was waning,"},{"time":16379,"text":"and he was sort of wondering, I think,"},{"time":18220,"text":"what would happen with society\nif there was no religion"},{"time":20834,"text":"or if there was less religion."},{"time":22318,"text":"And so he painted this famous painting,\n\"The Garden of Earthly Delights,\""},{"time":25796,"text":"which some have interpreted\nas being humanity before the Fall,"},{"time":29679,"text":"or being humanity without any Fall at all."},{"time":32941,"text":"And so it makes you wonder,"},{"time":34253,"text":"what would happen if we hadn't tasted\nthe fruit of knowledge, so to speak,"},{"time":37776,"text":"and what kind of morality would we have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41289,"text":"Much later, as a student,\nI went to a very different garden,"},{"time":44323,"text":"a zoological garden in Arnhem\nwhere we keep chimpanzees."},{"time":49015,"text":"This is me at an early age\nwith a baby chimpanzee."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52165,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":54874,"text":"And I discovered there"},{"time":56617,"text":"that the chimpanzees are very power-hungry\nand wrote a book about it."},{"time":59897,"text":"And at that time the focus\nin a lot of animal research"},{"time":62448,"text":"was on aggression and competition."},{"time":64899,"text":"I painted a whole picture\nof the animal kingdom"},{"time":67180,"text":"and humanity included, was that deep down\nwe are competitors, we are aggressive,"},{"time":72402,"text":"we are all out\nfor our own profit, basically."},{"time":75479,"text":"This is the launch of my book."},{"time":77375,"text":"I'm not sure how well\nthe chimpanzees read it,"},{"time":79783,"text":"but they surely seemed\ninterested in the book."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82478,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":84707,"text":"Now in the process of doing all this work"},{"time":87642,"text":"on power and dominance\nand aggression and so on,"},{"time":90566,"text":"I discovered that chimpanzees\nreconcile after fights."},{"time":93773,"text":"And so what you see here\nis two males who have had a fight."},{"time":96583,"text":"They ended up in a tree, and one of them\nholds out a hand to the other."},{"time":99951,"text":"And about a second\nafter I took the picture,"},{"time":102045,"text":"they came together in the fork of the tree"},{"time":104130,"text":"and kissed and embraced each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105870,"text":"And this is very interesting"},{"time":107238,"text":"because at the time, everything\nwas about competition and aggression,"},{"time":110559,"text":"so it wouldn't make any sense."},{"time":112077,"text":"The only thing that matters\nis that you win or you lose."},{"time":114737,"text":"But why reconcile after a fight?\nThat doesn't make any sense."},{"time":117698,"text":"This is the way bonobos do it.\nBonobos do everything with sex."},{"time":120720,"text":"And so they also reconcile with sex."},{"time":122558,"text":"But the principle is exactly the same."},{"time":124508,"text":"The principle is that you have\na valuable relationship"},{"time":128507,"text":"that is damaged by conflict,\nso you need to do something about it."},{"time":132621,"text":"So my whole picture of the animal kingdom,\nand including humans also,"},{"time":137012,"text":"started to change at that time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138975,"text":"So we have this image in political\nscience, economics, the humanities,"},{"time":142978,"text":"the philosophy for that matter,\nthat man is a wolf to man."},{"time":146860,"text":"And so deep down,\nour nature is actually nasty."},{"time":149973,"text":"I think it's a very unfair\nimage for the wolf."},{"time":152915,"text":"The wolf is, after all,\na very cooperative animal."},{"time":156385,"text":"And that's why many of you\nhave a dog at home,"},{"time":158663,"text":"which has all these characteristics also."},{"time":160906,"text":"And it's really unfair to humanity,"},{"time":162725,"text":"because humanity is actually\nmuch more cooperative and empathic"},{"time":166000,"text":"than given credit for."},{"time":168211,"text":"So I started getting\ninterested in those issues"},{"time":170495,"text":"and studying that in other animals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172830,"text":"So these are the pillars of morality."},{"time":174708,"text":"If you ask anyone,\n\"What is morality based on?\""},{"time":178284,"text":"these are the two factors\nthat always come out."},{"time":180503,"text":"One is reciprocity,"},{"time":182234,"text":"and associated with it is a sense\nof justice and a sense of fairness."},{"time":185813,"text":"And the other one is empathy\nand compassion."},{"time":188030,"text":"And human morality is more than this,\nbut if you would remove these two pillars,"},{"time":192305,"text":"there would be not much\nremaining, I think."},{"time":194458,"text":"So they're absolutely essential."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196137,"text":"So let me give you a few examples here."},{"time":198029,"text":"This is a very old video\nfrom the Yerkes Primate Center,"},{"time":200753,"text":"where they trained\nchimpanzees to cooperate."},{"time":203745,"text":"So this is already\nabout a hundred years ago"},{"time":206215,"text":"that we were doing\nexperiments on cooperation."},{"time":209331,"text":"What you have here is two\nyoung chimpanzees who have a box,"},{"time":212887,"text":"and the box is too heavy\nfor one chimp to pull in."},{"time":215916,"text":"And of course, there's food on the box."},{"time":217799,"text":"Otherwise they wouldn't\nbe pulling so hard."},{"time":219824,"text":"And so they're bringing in the box."},{"time":221961,"text":"And you can see that they're synchronized."},{"time":224254,"text":"You can see that they work together,\nthey pull at the same moment."},{"time":227378,"text":"It's already a big advance\nover many other animals"},{"time":229915,"text":"who wouldn't be able to do that."},{"time":231577,"text":"Now you're going to get\na more interesting picture,"},{"time":233987,"text":"because now one\nof the two chimps has been fed."},{"time":236637,"text":"So one of the two is not really interested\nin the task anymore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241908,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":248763,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":259794,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":263380,"text":"[- and sometimes appears to convey\nits wishes and meanings by gestures.]"},{"time":275760,"text":"Now look at what happens\nat the very end of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281380,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":292507,"text":"He takes basically everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294420,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":297420,"text":"There are two interesting\nparts about this."},{"time":299460,"text":"One is that the chimp on the right"},{"time":301126,"text":"has a full understanding\nhe needs the partner --"},{"time":303442,"text":"so a full understanding\nof the need for cooperation."},{"time":305901,"text":"The second one is that the partner\nis willing to work"},{"time":308414,"text":"even though he's not\ninterested in the food."},{"time":310560,"text":"Why would that be?"},{"time":311787,"text":"Well, that probably\nhas to do with reciprocity."},{"time":314002,"text":"There's actually a lot of evidence\nin primates and other animals"},{"time":317030,"text":"that they return favors."},{"time":318576,"text":"He will get a return favor\nat some point in the future."},{"time":321288,"text":"And so that's how this all operates."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324246,"text":"We do the same task with elephants."},{"time":325959,"text":"Now, it's very dangerous\nto work with elephants."},{"time":329137,"text":"Another problem with elephants\nis that you cannot make an apparatus"},{"time":332318,"text":"that is too heavy for a single elephant."},{"time":334259,"text":"Now you can probably make it,"},{"time":336000,"text":"but it's going to be a pretty\nclumsy apparatus, I think."},{"time":338785,"text":"And so what we did in that case --"},{"time":340451,"text":"we do these studies in Thailand\nfor Josh Plotnik --"},{"time":343137,"text":"is we have an apparatus around which\nthere is a rope, a single rope."},{"time":347094,"text":"And if you pull on this side of the rope,\nthe rope disappears on the other side."},{"time":350881,"text":"So two elephants need to pick it up\nat exactly the same time, and pull."},{"time":354292,"text":"Otherwise nothing is going to happen\nand the rope disappears."}]},{"cues":[{"time":357363,"text":"The first tape you're going to see"},{"time":359595,"text":"is two elephants who are released together\narrive at the apparatus."},{"time":363608,"text":"The apparatus is on the left,\nwith food on it."},{"time":366836,"text":"And so they come together,\nthey arrive together,"},{"time":369882,"text":"they pick it up together,\nand they pull together."},{"time":372199,"text":"So it's actually fairly simple for them."},{"time":376285,"text":"There they are."},{"time":385206,"text":"So that's how they bring it in."},{"time":386788,"text":"But now we're going to make it\nmore difficult."},{"time":388969,"text":"Because the purpose of this experiment"},{"time":390813,"text":"is to see how well\nthey understand cooperation."},{"time":393029,"text":"Do they understand that as well\nas the chimps, for example?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":395891,"text":"What we do in the next step is we release\none elephant before the other"},{"time":399393,"text":"and that elephant needs to be smart enough"},{"time":401428,"text":"to stay there and wait\nand not pull at the rope --"},{"time":403924,"text":"because if he pulls at the rope,\nit disappears and the whole test is over."},{"time":407429,"text":"Now this elephant does something illegal\nthat we did not teach it."},{"time":410723,"text":"But it shows the understanding he has,"},{"time":412913,"text":"because he puts his big foot on the rope,"},{"time":415461,"text":"stands on the rope\nand waits there for the other,"},{"time":417803,"text":"and then the other is going\nto do all the work for him."},{"time":420410,"text":"So it's what we call freeloading."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":426039,"text":"But it shows the intelligence\nthat the elephants have."},{"time":428879,"text":"They developed several\nof these alternative techniques"},{"time":431476,"text":"that we did not approve of, necessarily."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433458,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":434705,"text":"So the other elephant is now coming ..."},{"time":439746,"text":"and is going to pull it in."},{"time":459338,"text":"Now look at the other;\nit doesn't forget to eat, of course."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":465677,"text":"This was the cooperation\nand reciprocity part."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467918,"text":"Now something on empathy."},{"time":469161,"text":"Empathy is my main topic\nat the moment, of research."},{"time":471689,"text":"And empathy has two qualities:"},{"time":473161,"text":"One is the understanding part of it."},{"time":475204,"text":"This is just a regular definition:"},{"time":476859,"text":"the ability to understand and share\nthe feelings of another."},{"time":479695,"text":"And the emotional part."},{"time":480928,"text":"Empathy has basically two channels:\nOne is the body channel,"},{"time":484363,"text":"If you talk with a sad person,"},{"time":486245,"text":"you're going to adopt\na sad expression and a sad posture,"},{"time":489522,"text":"and before you know it, you feel sad."},{"time":491308,"text":"And that's sort of the body channel\nof emotional empathy,"},{"time":495550,"text":"which many animals have."},{"time":496853,"text":"Your average dog has that also."},{"time":498432,"text":"That's why people keep mammals in the home"},{"time":500456,"text":"and not turtles or snakes\nor something like that,"},{"time":502787,"text":"who don't have that kind of empathy."},{"time":504600,"text":"And then there's a cognitive channel,"},{"time":506396,"text":"which is more that you can take\nthe perspective of somebody else."},{"time":509484,"text":"And that's more limited."},{"time":510666,"text":"Very few animals, I think elephants\nand apes, can do that kind of thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516511,"text":"So synchronization,"},{"time":517897,"text":"which is part of that whole\nempathy mechanism,"},{"time":520064,"text":"is a very old one in the animal kingdom."},{"time":522343,"text":"In humans, of course,\nwe can study that with yawn contagion."},{"time":525608,"text":"Humans yawn when others yawn."},{"time":527450,"text":"And it's related to empathy."},{"time":529257,"text":"It activates the same areas in the brain."},{"time":531416,"text":"Also, we know that people\nwho have a lot of yawn contagion"},{"time":534161,"text":"are highly empathic."},{"time":535338,"text":"People who have problems with empathy,\nsuch as autistic children,"},{"time":538537,"text":"they don't have yawn contagion."},{"time":540053,"text":"So it is connected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541232,"text":"And we study that in our chimpanzees\nby presenting them with an animated head."},{"time":544979,"text":"So that's what you see on the upper-left,\nan animated head that yawns."},{"time":548994,"text":"And there's a chimpanzee watching,"},{"time":550638,"text":"an actual real chimpanzee\nwatching a computer screen"},{"time":553104,"text":"on which we play these animations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561331,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":563036,"text":"So yawn contagion\nthat you're probably all familiar with --"},{"time":566436,"text":"and maybe you're going\nto start yawning soon now --"},{"time":569139,"text":"is something that we share\nwith other animals."},{"time":572379,"text":"And that's related to that whole\nbody channel of synchronization"},{"time":575404,"text":"that underlies empathy,"},{"time":577148,"text":"and that is universal\nin the mammals, basically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580275,"text":"We also study more complex expressions --\nThis is consolation."},{"time":583410,"text":"This is a male chimpanzee\nwho has lost a fight and he's screaming,"},{"time":586534,"text":"and a juvenile comes over\nand puts an arm around him"},{"time":589269,"text":"and calms him down."},{"time":590458,"text":"That's consolation."},{"time":591656,"text":"It's very similar to human consolation."},{"time":593544,"text":"And consolation behavior --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":595727,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":596901,"text":"it's empathy driven."},{"time":598610,"text":"Actually, the way to study\nempathy in human children"},{"time":601451,"text":"is to instruct a family member\nto act distressed,"},{"time":604049,"text":"and then to see what young children do."},{"time":606036,"text":"And so it is related to empathy,"},{"time":608074,"text":"and that's the kind\nof expressions we look at."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610331,"text":"We also recently published an experiment\nyou may have heard about."},{"time":613453,"text":"It's on altruism and chimpanzees,"},{"time":615460,"text":"where the question is: Do chimpanzees care\nabout the welfare of somebody else?"},{"time":619900,"text":"And for decades it had been assumed\nthat only humans can do that,"},{"time":624375,"text":"that only humans worry\nabout the welfare of somebody else."},{"time":627658,"text":"Now we did a very simple experiment."},{"time":630119,"text":"We do that on chimpanzees\nthat live in Lawrenceville,"},{"time":632770,"text":"in the field station of Yerkes."},{"time":634536,"text":"And so that's how they live."},{"time":635897,"text":"And we call them into a room\nand do experiments with them."},{"time":639131,"text":"In this case, we put\ntwo chimpanzees side-by-side,"},{"time":641492,"text":"and one has a bucket full of tokens,\nand the tokens have different meanings."},{"time":645093,"text":"One kind of token feeds\nonly the partner who chooses,"},{"time":647690,"text":"the other one feeds both of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":649539,"text":"So this is a study we did\nwith Vicki Horner."},{"time":653556,"text":"And here, you have the two color tokens."},{"time":655849,"text":"So they have a whole bucket full of them."},{"time":657832,"text":"And they have to pick\none of the two colors."},{"time":661153,"text":"You will see how that goes."},{"time":663841,"text":"So if this chimp makes the selfish choice,"},{"time":667173,"text":"which is the red token in this case,"},{"time":669858,"text":"he needs to give it to us,"},{"time":671512,"text":"we pick it up, we put it on a table\nwhere there's two food rewards,"},{"time":674873,"text":"but in this case, only the one\non the right gets food."},{"time":677432,"text":"The one on the left walks away\nbecause she knows already"},{"time":680237,"text":"that this is not a good test for her."},{"time":682331,"text":"Then the next one is the pro-social token."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685040,"text":"So the one who makes the choices --\nthat's the interesting part here --"},{"time":688408,"text":"for the one who makes the choices,\nit doesn't really matter."},{"time":691252,"text":"So she gives us now a pro-social\ntoken and both chimps get fed."},{"time":694249,"text":"So the one who makes the choices\nalways gets a reward."},{"time":697000,"text":"So it doesn't matter whatsoever."},{"time":698602,"text":"And she should actually\nbe choosing blindly."},{"time":701922,"text":"But what we find is that they prefer\nthe pro-social token."},{"time":705305,"text":"So this is the 50 percent line,\nthat's the random expectation."},{"time":708323,"text":"And especially if the partner draws\nattention to itself, they choose more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712296,"text":"And if the partner\nputs pressure on them --"},{"time":714328,"text":"so if the partner starts spitting water\nand intimidating them --"},{"time":717491,"text":"then the choices go down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719043,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":720106,"text":"It's as if they're saying,"},{"time":722000,"text":"\"If you're not behaving,\nI'm not going to be pro-social today.\""},{"time":725011,"text":"And this is what happens\nwithout a partner,"},{"time":727039,"text":"when there's no partner sitting there."},{"time":728877,"text":"So we found that the chimpanzees do care\nabout the well-being of somebody else --"},{"time":732720,"text":"especially, these are other members\nof their own group."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736175,"text":"So the final experiment\nthat I want to mention to you"},{"time":738968,"text":"is our fairness study."},{"time":740639,"text":"And so this became a very famous study."},{"time":743553,"text":"And there are now many more,"},{"time":745000,"text":"because after we did this\nabout 10 years ago,"},{"time":747167,"text":"it became very well-known."},{"time":749524,"text":"And we did that originally\nwith Capuchin monkeys."},{"time":751841,"text":"And I'm going to show you\nthe first experiment that we did."},{"time":754655,"text":"It has now been done\nwith dogs and with birds"},{"time":757491,"text":"and with chimpanzees."},{"time":759545,"text":"But with Sarah Brosnan,\nwe started out with Capuchin monkeys."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764318,"text":"So what we did is we put\ntwo Capuchin monkeys side-by-side."},{"time":767547,"text":"Again, these animals, live in a group,\nthey know each other."},{"time":770400,"text":"We take them out of the group,\nput them in a test chamber."},{"time":773795,"text":"And there's a very simple task\nthat they need to do."},{"time":776365,"text":"And if you give both of them\ncucumber for the task,"},{"time":779769,"text":"the two monkeys side-by-side,"},{"time":781223,"text":"they're perfectly willing\nto do this 25 times in a row."},{"time":784077,"text":"So cucumber, even though\nit's only really water in my opinion,"},{"time":787548,"text":"but cucumber is perfectly fine for them."},{"time":790810,"text":"Now if you give the partner grapes --"},{"time":793117,"text":"the food preferences\nof my Capuchin monkeys"},{"time":795288,"text":"correspond exactly with the prices\nin the supermarket --"},{"time":798352,"text":"and so if you give them grapes --\nit's a far better food --"},{"time":801781,"text":"then you create inequity between them."},{"time":804702,"text":"So that's the experiment we did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806572,"text":"Recently, we videotaped it\nwith new monkeys"},{"time":808677,"text":"who'd never done the task,"},{"time":810038,"text":"thinking that maybe they would have\na stronger reaction,"},{"time":812694,"text":"and that turned out to be right."},{"time":814257,"text":"The one on the left is the monkey\nwho gets cucumber."},{"time":816777,"text":"The one on the right\nis the one who gets grapes."},{"time":819060,"text":"The one who gets cucumber --"},{"time":820431,"text":"note that the first piece\nof cucumber is perfectly fine."},{"time":823251,"text":"The first piece she eats."},{"time":825000,"text":"Then she sees the other one getting grape,\nand you will see what happens."},{"time":829294,"text":"So she gives a rock to us.\nThat's the task."},{"time":831897,"text":"And we give her a piece\nof cucumber and she eats it."},{"time":834979,"text":"The other one needs to give a rock to us."},{"time":838188,"text":"And that's what she does."},{"time":840587,"text":"And she gets a grape ..."},{"time":843579,"text":"and eats it."},{"time":844766,"text":"The other one sees that."},{"time":845985,"text":"She gives a rock to us now,"},{"time":847325,"text":"gets, again, cucumber."}]},{"cues":[{"time":852360,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":865741,"text":"(Laughter ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":867766,"text":"She tests a rock now against the wall."},{"time":870765,"text":"She needs to give it to us."},{"time":872984,"text":"And she gets cucumber again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":877343,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":884451,"text":"So this is basically\nthe Wall Street protest that you see here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887604,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":890000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":894277,"text":"I still have two minutes left --"},{"time":896087,"text":"let me tell you a funny story about this."},{"time":898261,"text":"This study became very famous\nand we got a lot of comments,"},{"time":901895,"text":"especially anthropologists,\neconomists, philosophers."},{"time":905525,"text":"They didn't like this at all."},{"time":906957,"text":"Because they had decided\nin their minds, I believe,"},{"time":909543,"text":"that fairness is a very complex issue,\nand that animals cannot have it."},{"time":914212,"text":"And so one philosopher even wrote us"},{"time":916699,"text":"that it was impossible that monkeys\nhad a sense of fairness"},{"time":919497,"text":"because fairness was invented\nduring the French Revolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922302,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":924743,"text":"And another one wrote a whole chapter"},{"time":927449,"text":"saying that he would believe\nit had something to do with fairness,"},{"time":931000,"text":"if the one who got grapes\nwould refuse the grapes."},{"time":933421,"text":"Now the funny thing is that Sarah Brosnan,\nwho's been doing this with chimpanzees,"},{"time":937317,"text":"had a couple of combinations\nof chimpanzees"},{"time":939487,"text":"where, indeed, the one\nwho would get the grape"},{"time":941867,"text":"would refuse the grape\nuntil the other guy also got a grape."},{"time":944797,"text":"So we're getting very close\nto the human sense of fairness."},{"time":947588,"text":"And I think philosophers need\nto rethink their philosophy for a while."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951658,"text":"So let me summarize."},{"time":953592,"text":"I believe there's an evolved morality."},{"time":955428,"text":"I think morality is much more\nthan what I've been talking about,"},{"time":958671,"text":"but it would be impossible\nwithout these ingredients"},{"time":961146,"text":"that we find in other primates,"},{"time":962668,"text":"which are empathy and consolation,"},{"time":964529,"text":"pro-social tendencies and reciprocity\nand a sense of fairness."},{"time":968259,"text":"And so we work on these particular issues"},{"time":970340,"text":"to see if we can create a morality\nfrom the bottom up, so to speak,"},{"time":973709,"text":"without necessarily\ngod and religion involved,"},{"time":976166,"text":"and to see how we can get\nto an evolved morality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":979066,"text":"And I thank you for your attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":980830,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}